 Of course all evil races are Kill on Sight, but certain factions within the light races are being seduced by the evil path. The straying lighties are not necessarily lost to evil, but they must be re-educated and redirected to the true path. <br><br>No light race should be dominant over another.<br>If we give in to this sentiment, and attack people simply because we can, we are no better than the evil races. If we hide behind the sentiment that it is because we are better than all the other races, we are worse than the evil ones.<br><br>Good NPC's should be protected, not killed.<br>NPC's should not be killed simply because they are good xp, or cash cows. This goes against all roleplaying ethics and degrades the game. It is difficult to aid these npc's, and most of what we do is of no help to them whatsoever, but we must try &lt;grin&gt;. This must be done carefully. We are not seeking to xp-kill any players. No NPC should be 'helped' after it has been pulled by a player, and no player in the process of killing one of these npc's should be hindered. However, if you are able to help before the innocent npc's are pulled, go for your life. Or if you are able to hinder a player camping an npc then do so. Help may be given in the form of summoned/gifted weapons buffs and damage shields, or any other imaginative way you can think of. Players killing innocent residents of Norrath should be made aware of the error of their distasteful ways. If they choose to ignore this warning, then they should be hindered. Hinderance, well, PvP server, take a wild stab in the dark. No, literally, take a wild stab in the dark &lt;grin&gt;. &lt;ooc&gt; This is not supposed to be done maliciously, or necessarily as a personal affront to the murderer, but is intended to be more tragedy/comedy than effective. Its intended to remind people that we're not just one side of a war, and it isnt supposed to be a historical simile of a struggle for territory, its supposed to be a Tolkenesque battle between the forces of good and evil. <br><br>N.B. NPC's are classed by their faction. It could be argued that 'good' and 'evil' are subjective concepts and what is good faction for one person, is bad for another, but lets not get into that argument, eh? For the purpose of this guild, good is the classical distinction. To preempt another comment... yes, you may not realise someone is good until you have killed them. Life is harsh, and in many cases, bad faction is harsher. The sentiment behind this philosophy is not to camp good NPC's out of hand. Sometimes it is unavoidable that good people lose their lives. We lament this fact, but we're at war. Casualties are inevitable. They have died for the greater good (ie specific items/quests), however, particularily good/easy xp/cash is not sufficient justification for their deaths. <br><br>General attitude...<br>People should behave in an honourable way, even if not being treated honourably, or reacting to a dishonourable person. Living or dying doesnt matter, 'winning' or 'losing' in a player confrontation depends upon how one holds onesself during that confrontation.<br><br>Oh yes, shouting 'Spawn check' is juste cause for instant guild removal. &lt;grin&gt;<br><br>Qualification for entrance...<br>To qualify for entrance you must be:<br>A good roleplayer<br>Above lvl 6.<br>A member of the Light team.<br>Insane.<br><br>If you are without guidance or ethical direction, and floundering in the turbulent times we are in. If you have yet to join a side in the war of Team Vs Team and Good Vs Evil that has suddenly returned. If you're bored doing the same old thing. Then come along and join this new guild.<br><br>Send me a tell in-game (Jukkar), or Email me at Jukkar@pimpdaddywelfare.com<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub77.ezboard.com/ftallonzektimes4735guildsoftallonzek.showPrevMessag